Body form and size.
Column tan or pink, smooth, ectoderm typically slightly wrinkled. Column stiff but not thick (about 
0.5 mm
); mesenterial insertions typically visible along entire length, most evident at limbus and margin. In some preserved specimens mesenteries protrude from proximal end of column or pedal disc (
Figure 5
).

Retractor muscles strong and diffuse (
Figure 6a
); in some specimens may be lobed. Parietobasilar muscles with no pennons or short detached ones.
